<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fælīvyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fælīvyn</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>fælyvd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fælevun</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>fælivd</orth></form></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обманывать</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>deceive</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>изменять</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>cheat</q></cit></sense></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fælyvd</orth></form></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fælītoj</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обманщик</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>deceiver</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>плут</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>cheat</q></cit></sense></sense></re></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_fælīvyn." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>afælyvta mæ sawærfyg ræsuǧd</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обманула меня чернобровая красавица</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a black-browed beauty deceived me</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>gædytæ ʒūry, fælītoj!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>врет он, плут!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he is lying, you cheat!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Qazaq"/><biblScope>153</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>afælyvta mæ sawærfyg ræsuǧd</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обманула меня чернобровая красавица</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a black-browed beauty deceived me</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>gædytæ ʒūry, fælītoj!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>врет он, плут!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he is lying, you cheat!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Qazaq"/><biblScope>153</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pati-raip-</w></mentioned>, сращение преверба %ifæ%i (←%ipati-%i) с не сохранившимся самостоятельно глаголом %iliv-%i (из %irip-%i с закономерным перебоем %ir%i → %iI%i перед %ii%i). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>firēftan : firēb-</w><gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>rēw</w><gloss><q>хитрость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>коварство</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>frēftan : frēp-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>brēp-</w><gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>βrβʼnt</w><gloss><q>обман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>rip-, lip-</w><gloss><q>мазать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>замазывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>обманывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>rip-</w><gloss><q>обман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>ripu-</w><gloss><q>обманщик</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>плут</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/><w>lip-</w><gloss><q>мазать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Исходное значение было ‘мазать’. Поэтому справедливо относят сюда же славянские глаголы со значением ‘лепить’, ‘клеить’ и пр. (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>лепить, липнуть</w></mentioned>); см. <bibl corresp="#ref_Walde—Pok."><biblScope>II 403</biblScope></bibl>. На иранской почве значение ‘мазать’ сохранилось в памирских: <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>rofam</w><gloss><q>я мажу</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Ср. д. <xr><ref target="#entry_ilivd"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 56, 87, III 156</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>20, 34, 61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pati-raip-</w></mentioned>, a contraction of the preverb %ifæ%i (←%ipati-%i) and a non-retained independently verb %iliv-%i (from %irip-%i with the regular change %ir%i → %iI%i before %ii%i). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>firēftan : firēb-</w><gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>rēw</w><gloss><q>slyness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>guile</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>frēftan : frēp-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>brēp-</w><gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>βrβʼnt</w><gloss><q>deception</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>rip-, lip-</w><gloss><q>paint</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>smear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>deceive</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>rip-</w><gloss><q>deception</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>ripu-</w><gloss><q>deceiver</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>cheat</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/><w>lip-</w><gloss><q>paint</q></gloss></mentioned>. The initial meaning was ‘smear’. That is why Slavic verb with the meaning ‘mould’, ‘glue’ etc. are also related to it (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>лепить</w><gloss><q>stick</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>липнуть</w><gloss><q>be sticky</q></gloss></mentioned>, ); see <bibl corresp="#ref_Walde—Pok."><biblScope>II 403</biblScope></bibl>. In the Iranian languages, the meaning ‘smear’ is retained in Pamir languages: <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>rofam</w><gloss><q>I am smearing</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Cf. Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_ilivd"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 56, 87, III 156</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>20, 34, 61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>